column1: Addition of chlorine to water gives both hydrochloric acid (HCl) and hypochlorous acid (HOCl): Cl2 + H2O ⇌ HClO + HCl Cl2 + 4 OH− ⇌ 2 ClO− + 2 H2O + 2 e− Cl2 + 2 e− ⇌ 2 Cl− When acids are added to aqueous salts of hypochlorous acid (such as sodium hypochlorite in commercial bleach solution), the resultant reaction is driven to the left, and chlorine gas is formed.
column2: H g O ( a q ) + 2 C l 2 ( g ) + H 2 O ( l ) → H g C l 2 ( a q ) + 2 H C l O ( a q ) {\displaystyle \mathrm {HgO} (aq)+2\mathrm {Cl_{2}} (g)+\mathrm {H_{2}O} (l)\rightarrow \mathrm {HgCl_{2}} (aq)+2\mathrm {HClO} (aq)} Penambahan klorin ke dalam air menghasilkan asam klorida (HCl) dan asam hipoklorit (HOCl): Cl2 + H2O HClO + HCl Cl2 + 4 OH− 2 ClO− + 2 H2O + 2 e− Cl2 + 2 e− 2 Cl− Ketika asam ditambahkan dengan larutan garam asam hipoklorit (seperti natrium hipoklorit dalam larutan pemutih komersil), reaksi yang dihasilkan mengarah ke sebelah kiri (reaktan), dan gas klorin terbentuk.
